President Cyril Ramaphosa during his State of the Nation Address highlighted issues involving Eskom, land, SOEs, the National Health Insurance and housing. On land, he announced that this year, the government will implement key recommendations of the Presidential Advisory Panel on Land Reform and Agriculture to accelerate land redistribution, expand agricultural production and transform the industry. Ramaphosa also announced a plan to expand the district development model to 23 new districts, drawing on lessons from the three pilot districts in OR Tambo District Municipality, Ethekwini and Waterberg District Municipality. Below is an infographic showing highlights of SONA 2020: 